    ["PRIESTSHADOWRAIDSTROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n\n[1] Precast Mind Blast\n[2] Cast Tentacle Slam\n[3] Cast Shadow Word: Pain\n[4] Cast Voidform\n[5] Cast Power Infusion + Use Tempered Potion + Any on use trinkets\n[6] Cast Void Volley\n[7] Cast Shadow Word: Madness\n[8] Cast Void Torrent\n[9] Cast Void Blast\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n[1] Cast Shadow Word: Pain to maintain Shadow Word: Pain\n[2] Maintain Vampiric Touch, either with Tentacle Slam or hard cast Vampiric Touch\n[3] Cast Voidform to enter Voidform\n[4] Cast Power Infusion\n[5] Cast Shadow Word: Death if the target has an absorb shield\n[6] Cast Void Blast if Shadow Word: Madness is active or if Entropic Rift is about to expire\n[7] Spend Insanity on Shadow Word: Madness if it is not active, is about to fall off, you are about to cap, or Entropic Rift is active\n[8] Cast Void Volley\n[9] Cast Void Torrent to activate Entropic Rift\n[10] Cast Mind Blast\n[11] Cast Shadow Word: Madness\n[12] Cast Tentacle Slam if there will be no additional targets to DoT or upcoming movement\n[13] Cast Mind Flay, interrupting as soon as anything of higher priority becomes available\n[14] When moving, cast Tentacle Slam, Shadow Word: Death, or Shadow Word: Pain to generate some Insanity and deal some damage",
    ["PRIESTSHADOWDELVEROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n\n[1] Precast Mind Blast\n[2] Cast Tentacle Slam\n[3] Cast Shadow Word: Pain\n[4] Cast Voidform\n[5] Cast Power Infusion + Use Tempered Potion + Any on use trinkets\n[6] Cast Void Volley\n[7] Cast Shadow Word: Madness\n[8] Cast Void Torrent\n[9] Cast Void Blast\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n[1] Cast Shadow Word: Pain to maintain Shadow Word: Pain\n[2] Maintain Vampiric Touch, either with Tentacle Slam or hard cast Vampiric Touch\n[3] Cast Voidform to enter Voidform\n[4] Cast Power Infusion\n[5] Cast Shadow Word: Death if the target has an absorb shield\n[6] Cast Void Blast if Shadow Word: Madness is active or if Entropic Rift is about to expire\n[7] Spend Insanity on Shadow Word: Madness if it is not active, is about to fall off, you are about to cap, or Entropic Rift is active\n[8] Cast Void Volley\n[9] Cast Void Torrent to activate Entropic Rift\n[10] Cast Mind Blast\n[11] Cast Shadow Word: Madness\n[12] Cast Tentacle Slam if there will be no additional targets to DoT or upcoming movement\n[13] Cast Mind Flay, interrupting as soon as anything of higher priority becomes available\n[14] When moving, cast Tentacle Slam, Shadow Word: Death, or Shadow Word: Pain to generate some Insanity and deal some damage",
    ["PRIESTDISCIPLINERAIDROTATION"] = "[1] Refresh Shadow Word: Pain on your enemies if the duration is less than 20 seconds.\n[2] Cast Flash Heal on an injured ally, this also applies Atonement to yourself.\n[3] Use Penance defensively.\n[4] Cast Power Word: Shield.\n[5] Cast Plea.\n[6] Cast Power Word: Radiances back to back, preferring one cast on melee and one on ranged if allies are spread out.\n[7] Cast Shadow Word: Death always on cooldown, even if the target is out of execute range, this triggers Expiation value which is very high damage.\n[8] Use Penance defensively to heal an injured ally.\n[9] Cast Mind Blast, this will empower your next Penance with Dark Indulgence.\n[10] Use Penance defensively to heal an injured ally.\n[11] Spam Smite.\n[12] Cast Power Word: Shield any time your Apex Talent Void Shield activates.\n[13] Mini-Ramps will set up healing in a similar way, minus Evangelism, meaning you will use more Pleas.",
    ["PRIESTDISCIPLINEDELVEROTATION"] = "[1] Maintain/refresh Shadow Word: Pain. It is much stronger in Midnight so you will want to make sure you are applying at least one and then letting Penance spread the DoT.\n[2] Use Evangelism (or Power Word: Radiance if Evang is on cd) to apply Atonements to allies.\n[3] Cast Shadow Word: Death always on cooldown, even if the target is out of execute range, this triggers Expiation value which is very high damage.\n[4] Cast Mind Blast\n[5] Cast Penance\n[6] Cast Shadow Word: Death always on cooldown, even if the target is out of execute range.\n[7] Spam Void Blast and use Penance on cooldown.\n[8] Use Power Word: Shield on cooldown during downtime.",
    ["PRIESTDISCIPLINEDUNGEONROTATION"] = "[1] Maintain/refresh Shadow Word: Pain. It is much stronger in Midnight so you will want to make sure you are applying at least one and then letting Penance spread the DoT.\n[2] Use Evangelism (or Power Word: Radiance if Evang is on cd) to apply Atonements to allies.\n[3] Cast Shadow Word: Death always on cooldown, even if the target is out of execute range, this triggers Expiation value which is very high damage.\n[4] Cast Mind Blast\n[5] Cast Penance\n[6] Cast Shadow Word: Death always on cooldown, even if the target is out of execute range.\n[7] Spam Void Blast and use Penance on cooldown.\n[8] Use Power Word: Shield on cooldown during downtime.\n2. Use Evangelism (or Power Word: Radiance if Evang is on cd) to apply Atonements to allies.\n\n3. Cast Shadow Word: Death always on cooldown, even if the target is out of execute range, this triggers Expiation value which is very high damage.\n\n4. Cast Penance defensively on allies.\n\n5. Cast Mind Blast.\n\n6. Cast Penance defensively on allies.\n\n7. Cast Shadow Word: Death on cd.\n\n8. Spam Smite and use Penance on cooldown.\n\n9. Use Power Word: Shield on every Void Shield proc.\n\n10. Watch for Shadow Mend procs and weave them in as needed.",
    ["PRIESTHOLYDELVEROTATION"] = "[1] Cast Halo frequently for healing and damage, look to utilize before incoming damage so you can start generating Surge of Light procs to help with healing (these heal for more than regular casts!).\n[2] Cast Holy Word: Serenity on cooldown for single target.\n[3] Keep Prayer of Mending on cooldown. (Focus on refreshing/maintaining stacks on players).\n[4] Use Apotheosis frequently to save mana, reset the cooldowns of your Holy Words to prepare for additional burst damage or simply as a damage cooldown during downtime.\n[5] Use Flash Heal to build up stacks of Lightweaver to spend on more powerful Prayer of Healing casts.",
    ["PRIESTHOLYRAIDROTATION"] = "[1] Use Flash Heal to build up stacks of Lightweaver to spend on more powerful Prayer of Healing casts.\n[2] Cast Holy Word: Serenity for single target healing on cooldown.\n[3] Consume any Surge of Light procs on Prayer of Healing whenever possible, you can hold up to two stacks.\n[4] Keep Prayer of Mending on cooldown.\n[5] Cast Flash Heals to spot-heal as needed.\n[6] Cast Smite during downtime to farm for Surge of Light procs.\n[7] Cast Divine Hymn for raid-wide damage.",
    ["PRIESTHOLYDUNGEONROTATION"] = "[1] Cast Halo frequently for healing and damage, look to utilize before incoming damage so you can start generating Surge of Light procs to help with healing (these heal for more than regular casts!).\n[2] Cast Holy Word: Serenity on cooldown for single target.\n[3] Keep Prayer of Mending on cooldown. (Focus on refreshing/maintaining stacks on players).\n[4] Use Apotheosis frequently to save mana, reset the cooldowns of your Holy Words to prepare for additional burst damage or simply as a damage cooldown during downtime.\n[5] Use Flash Heal to build up stacks of Lightweaver to spend on more powerful Prayer of Healing casts.",
    ["DRUIDBALANCEDUNGEONROTATION"] = "1. Spread Moonfire while targets are being gathered.\n\n2. Apply Sunfire when all targets are gathered.\n\n3. Press Force of Nature if you have Incarnation: Chosen of Elune available or if Force of Nature will be available again before Incarnation: Chosen of Elune.\n\n4. Press Incarnation: Chosen of Elune if you just used Force of Nature.\n\n5. Cast Starsurge to consume Starweaver's Weft.\n\n6. Cast Starfire at the start of Incarnation: Chosen of Elune to consume Ascendant Fires.\n\n7. Cast Starfall to prevent capping on Astral Power or to consume Ascendant Eclipses at the start of Eclipse.\n\n8. Cast Wrath outside of Eclipse up to and including 6 targets.\n\n9. Cast Starfire in Lunar Eclipse and Wrath in Solar Eclipse.",
