    ["DEATHKNIGHTUNHOLYRAIDSTMAXROLL"] = "CwPAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAwMjZMzYY2mZmZa2MzMjZAAAAAAAAgZeAmZAwyMmZ2mZGzYGwmZxwADMbM0YBAzAAzMjZAmZmxMG",
    ["DEATHKNIGHTUNHOLYRAIDSTROTATION"] = "--Opener--\n\n1. Use Outbreak when not running Blightburst.\n\n2. Use 2x Festering Strike.\n\n3. Use Army of the Dead + Dark Transformation + Trinket + Racial + Potion\n\n4. Use Soul Reaper.\n\n5. When it comes to timing your trinkets, you can just macro them with Army of the Dead in all your openers. If you are lucky enough for receive Power Infusion, ask for it when you cast Army of the Dead.\n\n6. The timing of Soul Reaper (with Pestilence talented) in the opener is to overlap the plague damage debuff for when you consume Pestilence after Dark Transformation\n\n--Rotation--\n\n1. Use Outbreak to maintain your plagues on the target.\n\n2. Use Festering Scythe if its debuff has fallen off.\n\n3. Use Soul Reaper if the enemy is below 35% health or you have triggered the Reaping effect from Dark Transformation.\n\n4. Use Scourge Strike when you have 4+ Runes and at least one stack of Lesser Ghoul.\n\n5. Use Death Coil when you have a Sudden Doom proc or 80+ Runic Power.\n\n6. Use Putrefy if the target is above 35% health. If your target is below 35%, use Soul Reaper to trigger your Putrefy instead.\n\n7. Use Festering Strike if you have less than 3 stacks of Lesser Ghoul.\n\n8. Use Scourge Strike if you have at least 1 stack of Lesser Ghoul.\n\n9. Use Death Coil.\n\n10. Now, we will take this priority list and put it into a wordier description!\n\n11. Maintain your Plagues on the target by leveraging Outbreak. Your plagues do not only do damage but are also the source of your important Sudden Doom procs so keeping them up is crucial.\n\n12. Cast Soul Reaper whenever you can. Either when the target is below 35% health or you have received the free use from Dark Transformation with Reaping.\n\n13. Use Death Coil to avoid capping Runic Power or to spend your procs of Sudden Doom. Sudden Doom is a powerful proc, and you do not want to waste any. If you have Harbinger of Doom talented, you can allow yourself to stack up two charges before you spend them. However, most of the time, you simply use them as soon as possible to avoid any potential waste. We also do not want to overcap Runic Power (generating Runic Power when we are at 100), so we use Death Coil to avoid this. However, you should prioritise Scourge Strike if you are at 4+ Runes. It is more important to avoid overcapping Runes compared to Runic Power in Single Target.\n\n14. Use Festering Strike to build up stacks of Lesser Ghoul on yourself. We want to aim for between 4 and 6 stacks at all times to give ourself some flexbility, either when we are forced out of melee range or if you we need to prioritise Scourge Strike due to Trollbane's Icy Fury. We also use Festering Scythe as a high priority if its debuff has fallen off. Your normal rotation will usally take care of this but it is still important to track\n\n15. Use Scourge Strike to consume your stacks of Lesser Ghoul. This is used in sync with Festering Strike to keep your stack count at a healthy level. You go up to 4-6 and then use Scourge Strike to drop down to 3 again.\n\n16. Use Death Coil as your filler spell when you have nothing else to do!",
