    ["DEMONHUNTERHAVOCRAIDSTROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Cast Immolation Aura 1 GCD Pre-Pull\n\n2. Use Fleeting Tempered Potion and any on-use trinkets such as Araz's Ritual Forge.\n\n3. Cast The Hunt\n\n4. Cast Felblade\n\n5. Cast Eye Beam\n\n6. Cast Essence Break\n\n7. Cast Death Sweep\n\n8. Cast Death Sweep\n\n9. Cast Annihilation\n\n10. Cast Vengeful Retreat and Metamorphosis\n\n11. Cast Death Sweep\n\n12. Cast Fel Rush\n\n13. Cast Annihilation\n\n14. Cast Consuming Fire\n\n15. Cast Abyssal Gaze\n\n16. Continue with normal priority\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. If Inertia buff is up, Cast Felblade or Fel Rush to proc.\n\n2. Cast The Hunt.\n\n3. Cast Death Sweep.\n\n4. Cast Vengeful Retreat if Eye Beam is off cooldown.\n\n5. Cast Eye Beam.\n\n6. Cast Essence Break while in Metamorphosis.\n\n7. Cast Metamorphosis.\n\n8. Cast Blade Dance.\n\n9. Cast Annihilation.\n\n10. Cast Chaos Strike.\n\n11. Cast Immolation Aura.\n\n12. Cast Felblade.\n\n13. Cast Throw Glaive or Fel Rush when no other abilities are available.",
    ["DEMONHUNTERVENGEANCEDUNGEONROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Precast Sigil of Flame in single-target or on a single pack.\n\n2. Infernal Strike into the enemy (or edge of enemies if there are multiple).\n\n3. Use Spirit Bomb as you Infernal Strike in if you have Souls and Fury saved from the previous pull.\n\n4. Use Immolation Aura.\n\n5. Use Fracture to generate Souls and Fury.\n\n6. Use Fiery Brand for Fire damage buff.\n\n7. Use Sigil of Spite.\n\n8. Use Spirit Bomb with 6 Souls.\n\n9. Use Felblade to generate Fury if you don't have enough.\n\n10. Fully channel Fel Devastation for Souls.\n\n11. Use Metamorphosis once enemies are grouped.\n\n12. Use Fracture until you are at 6 Souls.\n\n13. Use Spirit Bomb with 6 Souls.\n\n14. Use Soul Cleave with 0 Souls.\n\n15. Continue to Main Rotation.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Use Infernal Strike off GCD if you are at or near 2 charges and will not need it for movement soon.\n\n2. Use Metamorphosis if you will not overcap duration and Spirit Bomb has more than 10s remaining on its CD.\n\n3. Use Fracture at or near 2 charges.\n\n4. Use Spirit Bomb with 4+ Souls if Fiery Brand is about to run out.\n\n5. Use Fiery Brand if the debuff is not currently active.\n\n6. Use Spirit Bomb with 6 Souls.\n\n7. Use Immolation Aura.\n\n8. Use Sigil of Flame.\n\n9. Use Sigil of Spite if you will not cap Souls.\n\n10. Use Felblade if you have 6 Souls but not enough Fury to Spirit Bomb.\n\n11. Use Fel Devastation if you have at least 50 Fury.\n\n12. Spend Fury and any available Souls with Soul Cleave.\n\n13. Use Fracture if you won't cap Souls.\n\n14. Use Felblade if you won't cap Fury.\n\n15. Use Throw Glaive for filler or when kiting.",
    ["DEMONHUNTERVENGEANCEDELVEROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Precast Sigil of Flame in single-target or on a single pack.\n\n2. Infernal Strike into the enemy (or edge of enemies if there are multiple).\n\n3. Use Spirit Bomb as you Infernal Strike in if you have Souls and Fury saved from the previous pull.\n\n4. Use Immolation Aura.\n\n5. Use Fracture to generate Souls and Fury.\n\n6. Use Fiery Brand for Fire damage buff.\n\n7. Use Sigil of Spite.\n\n8. Use Spirit Bomb with 6 Souls.\n\n9. Use Felblade to generate Fury if you don't have enough.\n\n10. Fully channel Fel Devastation for Souls.\n\n11. Use Metamorphosis once enemies are grouped.\n\n12. Use Fracture until you are at 6 Souls.\n\n13. Use Spirit Bomb with 6 Souls.\n\n14. Use Soul Cleave with 0 Souls.\n\n15. Continue to Main Rotation.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Use Infernal Strike off GCD if you are at or near 2 charges and will not need it for movement soon.\n\n2. Use Metamorphosis if you will not overcap duration and Spirit Bomb has more than 10s remaining on its CD.\n\n3. Use Fracture at or near 2 charges.\n\n4. Use Spirit Bomb with 4+ Souls if Fiery Brand is about to run out.\n\n5. Use Fiery Brand if the debuff is not currently active.\n\n6. Use Spirit Bomb with 6 Souls.\n\n7. Use Immolation Aura.\n\n8. Use Sigil of Flame.\n\n9. Use Sigil of Spite if you will not cap Souls.\n\n10. Use Felblade if you have 6 Souls but not enough Fury to Spirit Bomb.\n\n11. Use Fel Devastation if you have at least 50 Fury.\n\n12. Spend Fury and any available Souls with Soul Cleave.\n\n13. Use Fracture if you won't cap Souls.\n\n14. Use Felblade if you won't cap Fury.\n\n15. Use Throw Glaive for filler or when kiting.",
    ["DEMONHUNTERVENGEANCERAIDROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Precast Sigil of Flame in single-target or on a single pack.\n\n2. Infernal Strike into the enemy (or edge of enemies if there are multiple).\n\n3. Use Spirit Bomb as you Infernal Strike in if you have Souls and Fury saved from the previous pull.\n\n4. Use Immolation Aura.\n\n5. Use Fracture to generate Souls and Fury.\n\n6. Use Fiery Brand for Fire damage buff.\n\n7. Use Sigil of Spite.\n\n8. Use Spirit Bomb with 6 Souls.\n\n9. Use Felblade to generate Fury if you don't have enough.\n\n10. Fully channel Fel Devastation for Souls.\n\n11. Use Metamorphosis once enemies are grouped.\n\n12. Use Fracture until you are at 6 Souls.\n\n13. Use Spirit Bomb with 6 Souls.\n\n14. Use Soul Cleave with 0 Souls.\n\n15. Continue to Main Rotation.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Use Infernal Strike off GCD if you are at or near 2 charges and will not need it for movement soon.\n\n2. Use Metamorphosis if you will not overcap duration and Spirit Bomb has more than 10s remaining on its CD.\n\n3. Use Fracture if you are at or near 2 charges.\n\n4. Use Spirit Bomb with 4+ Souls if Fiery Brand is about to run out.\n\n5. Use Fiery Brand if the debuff is not currently active.\n\n6. Use Spirit Bomb with 6 Souls.\n\n7. Use Immolation Aura.\n\n8. Use Sigil of Flame.\n\n9. Use Sigil of Spite if you will not overcap Souls.\n\n10. Use Soul Cleave with 1 or more Souls.\n\n11. Use Fel Devastation if you have at least 50 Fury.\n\n12. Spend Fury with Soul Cleave at 0 Souls.\n\n13. Use Fracture if you won't cap Fury or Souls.\n\n14. Use Felblade if you won't cap Fury.\n\n15. Use Throw Glaive for filler or when kiting.",
    ["DRUIDRESTORATIONDUNGEONROTATION"] = "1. Keep Efflorescence active at all times. If you are running Lifetreading (and the default build does) then keeping Lifebloom up does this for you.\n\n2. Keep Lifebloom up at all times. This is crucial and Lifebloom will make up a lot of your dungeon healing via our Apex, Everbloom.\n\n3. Cast Swiftmend on cooldown, even if the party is reasonably healthy. It'll proc Power of the Archdruid which will put out two Rejuvenations, and Verdant Infusion will extend HoTs on your target.\n\n4. Cast Wild Growth during moderate damage periods, or to top the group up after minor damage. It's extremely GCD efficient, and also adds a Mastery stack to everyone in your group.\n\n5. React to anyone dropping very low with Nature's Swiftness + Regrowth, or just Regrowth depending on what is available.\n\n6. Fill any free time by contributing DPS. We'll cover that in detail below.",
    ["DRUIDRESTORATIONDELVEROTATION"] = "1. Keep Efflorescence active at all times. If you are running Lifetreading (and the default build does) then keeping Lifebloom up does this for you.\n\n2. Keep Lifebloom up at all times. This is crucial and Lifebloom will make up a lot of your dungeon healing via our Apex, Everbloom.\n\n3. Cast Swiftmend on cooldown, even if the party is reasonably healthy. It'll proc Power of the Archdruid which will put out two Rejuvenations, and Verdant Infusion will extend HoTs on your target.\n\n4. Cast Wild Growth during moderate damage periods, or to top the group up after minor damage. It's extremely GCD efficient, and also adds a Mastery stack to everyone in your group.\n\n5. React to anyone dropping very low with Nature's Swiftness + Regrowth, or just Regrowth depending on what is available.\n\n6. Fill any free time by contributing DPS. We'll cover that in detail below.",
    ["DRUIDRESTORATIONRAIDROTATION"] = "1. Begin your Rejuvenation ramp ~15 seconds before damage hits.\n\n2. Hit Swiftmend followed by Rejuvenation. The Swiftmend procs Soul of the Forest, which will give you two free superpowered Rejuvenation buffs on the follow-up cast.\n\n3. The Swiftmend and Wild Growth casts automatically proc Grove Guardians which will significantly buff your healing.\n\n4. Convoke is your short-cooldown burst heal, and it has about a 50% chance to proc a mini-Flourish which will extend your Rejuvenation buffs.",
    ["DRUIDGUARDIANDUNGEONROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Cast Red Moon on cooldown.\n\n2. Cast Mangle on cooldown.\n\n3. Cast Thrash on cooldown.\n\n4. Maintain 3-5 stacks of Thrash.\n\n5. Spend Rage on either Maul (offensively) or Ironfur (defensively).\n\n6. Cast Frenzied Regeneration if your health dips low.\n\n7. Use your cooldowns Barkskin / Incarnation: Guardian of Ursoc as frequently as possible.\n\n8. Cast Swipe if you have nothing else to press.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Maintain Moonfire on your primary target.\n\n2. Maintain 3-5 stacks of Thrash.\n\n3. Cast Mangle on cooldown.\n\n4. Cast Thrash on cooldown.\n\n5. Spend Rage on either Maul (offensively) or Ironfur (defensively).\n\n6. Cast Frenzied Regeneration if your health dips low.\n\n7. Cast Moonfire with Galactic Guardian procs.\n\n8. Use your cooldowns Barkskin / Incarnation: Guardian of Ursoc as frequently as possible.\n\n9. Cast Swipe if you have nothing else to press.",
    ["DRUIDGUARDIANDELVEROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Cast Red Moon on cooldown.\n\n2. Cast Mangle on cooldown.\n\n3. Cast Thrash on cooldown.\n\n4. Maintain 3-5 stacks of Thrash.\n\n5. Spend Rage on either Maul (offensively) or Ironfur (defensively).\n\n6. Cast Frenzied Regeneration if your health dips low.\n\n7. Use your cooldowns Barkskin / Incarnation: Guardian of Ursoc as frequently as possible.\n\n8. Cast Swipe if you have nothing else to press.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Maintain Moonfire on your primary target.\n\n2. Maintain 3-5 stacks of Thrash.\n\n3. Cast Mangle on cooldown.\n\n4. Cast Thrash on cooldown.\n\n5. Spend Rage on either Maul (offensively) or Ironfur (defensively).\n\n6. Cast Frenzied Regeneration if your health dips low.\n\n7. Cast Moonfire with Galactic Guardian procs.\n\n8. Use your cooldowns Barkskin / Incarnation: Guardian of Ursoc as frequently as possible.\n\n9. Cast Swipe if you have nothing else to press.",
    ["DRUIDGUARDIANRAIDROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Cast Red Moon on cooldown.\n\n2. Cast Mangle on cooldown.\n\n3. Cast Thrash on cooldown.\n\n4. Maintain 3-5 stacks of Thrash.\n\n5. Spend Rage on either Maul (offensively) or Ironfur (defensively).\n\n6. Cast Frenzied Regeneration if your health dips low.\n\n7. Use your cooldowns Barkskin / Incarnation: Guardian of Ursoc as frequently as possible.\n\n8. Cast Swipe if you have nothing else to press.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Maintain Moonfire on your primary target.\n\n2. Maintain 3-5 stacks of Thrash.\n\n3. Cast Red Moon on cooldown.\n\n4. Cast Mangle on cooldown.\n\n5. Cast Thrash on cooldown.\n\n6. Spend Rage on either Maul (offensively) or Ironfur (defensively).\n\n7. Cast Frenzied Regeneration if your health dips low.\n\n8. Cast Moonfire with Galactic Guardian procs.\n\n9. Use your cooldowns Barkskin / Incarnation: Guardian of Ursoc as frequently as possible.\n\n10. Cast Swipe if you have nothing else to press.",
    ["DRUIDFERALDUNGEONROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Rake from stealth.\n\n2. Shred to 5 Combo Points.\n\n3. Cast Berserk and Tiger's Fury.\n\n4. Cast Rip.\n\n5. Cast Convoke the Spirits.\n\n6. Cast Ferocious Bite after Convoke the Spirits.\n\n7. Cast Feral Frenzy.\n\n8. Cast Ferocious Bite at 5 Combo Points and Shred to generate Combo Points during Berserk.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Cast Primal Wrath if Rip is missing or in pandemic.\n\n2. Cast Berserk with Tiger's Fury, these should be synced.\n\n3. Cast Ferocious Bite if you have 5 Combo Points and Rip is active.\n\n4. Berserk and Convoke the Spirits with Tiger's Fury, these should be synced.\n\n5. Cast Tiger's Fury on cooldown.\n\n6. Cast Feral Frenzy on cooldown.\n\n7. Swipe to generate Combo points.",
    ["DRUIDFERALDELVEROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Rake from stealth.\n\n2. Shred to 5 Combo Points.\n\n3. Cast Berserk and Tiger's Fury.\n\n4. Cast Rip.\n\n5. Cast Convoke the Spirits.\n\n6. Cast Ferocious Bite after Convoke the Spirits.\n\n7. Cast Feral Frenzy.\n\n8. Cast Ferocious Bite at 5 Combo Points and Shred to generate Combo Points during Berserk.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Cast Primal Wrath if Rip is missing or in pandemic.\n\n2. Cast Berserk with Tiger's Fury, these should be synced.\n\n3. Cast Ferocious Bite if you have 5 Combo Points and Rip is active.\n\n4. Berserk and Convoke the Spirits with Tiger's Fury, these should be synced.\n\n5. Cast Tiger's Fury on cooldown.\n\n6. Cast Feral Frenzy on cooldown.\n\n7. Swipe to generate Combo points.",
    ["DRUIDFERALRAIDAOEROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Rake from stealth.\n\n2. Shred to 5 Combo Points.\n\n3. Cast Berserk and Tiger's Fury.\n\n4. Cast Rip.\n\n5. Cast Convoke the Spirits.\n\n6. Cast Ferocious Bite after Convoke the Spirits.\n\n7. Cast Feral Frenzy.\n\n8. Cast Ferocious Bite at 5 Combo Points and Shred to generate Combo Points during Berserk.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Cast Primal Wrath if Rip is missing or in pandemic.\n\n2. Cast Berserk with Tiger's Fury, these should be synced.\n\n3. Cast Ferocious Bite if you have 5 Combo Points and Rip is active.\n\n4. Berserk and Convoke the Spirits with Tiger's Fury, these should be synced.\n\n5. Cast Tiger's Fury on cooldown.\n\n6. Cast Feral Frenzy on cooldown.\n\n7. Swipe to generate Combo points.",
    ["DRUIDFERALRAIDSTROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Rake from stealth.\n\n2. Shred to 5 Combo Points.\n\n3. Cast Berserk and Tiger's Fury.\n\n4. Cast Rip.\n\n5. Cast Convoke the Spirits.\n\n6. Cast Ferocious Bite after Convoke the Spirits.\n\n7. Cast Feral Frenzy.\n\n8. Cast Ferocious Bite at 5 Combo Points and Shred to generate Combo Points during Berserk.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Cast Rip if it is missing on the target, or if it is in Pandemic and you have 5 Combo Points.\n\n2. Cast Ferocious Bite if you have 4 or more Combo Points, 25 or greater energy, and Rip is active.\n\n3. Berserk and Convoke the Spirits with Tiger's Fury, these should be synced.\n\n4. Cast Feral Frenzy with Tiger's Fury active.\n\n5. If Tiger's Fury is coming off CD within 3 seconds, and you're above 80% energy, dump your energy.\n\n6. Cast Feral Frenzy on cooldown.\n\n7. Cast Tiger's Fury on cooldown.\n\n8. Cast Rake if it is missing on the target or in pandemic.\n\n9. Shred to Generate Combo Points.",
    ["DRUIDBALANCERAIDAOEROTATION"] = "1. Spread Moonfire while targets are being gathered.\n\n2. Apply Sunfire when all targets are gathered.\n\n3. Press Force of Nature if you have Incarnation: Chosen of Elune available or if Force of Nature will be available again before Incarnation: Chosen of Elune.\n\n4. Press Incarnation: Chosen of Elune if you just used Force of Nature.\n\n5. Cast Starsurge to consume Starweaver's Weft.\n\n6. Cast Starfire at the start of Incarnation: Chosen of Elune to consume Ascendant Fires.\n\n7. Cast Starfall to prevent capping on Astral Power or to consume Ascendant Eclipses at the start of Eclipse.\n\n8. Cast Wrath outside of Eclipse up to and including 6 targets.\n\n9. Cast Starfire in Lunar Eclipse and Wrath in Solar Eclipse.",
    ["DRUIDBALANCEDELVEROTATION"] = "1. Spread Moonfire while targets are being gathered.\n\n2. Apply Sunfire when all targets are gathered.\n\n3. Press Force of Nature if you have Incarnation: Chosen of Elune available or if Force of Nature will be available again before Incarnation: Chosen of Elune.\n\n4. Press Incarnation: Chosen of Elune if you just used Force of Nature.\n\n5. Cast Starsurge to consume Starweaver's Weft.\n\n6. Cast Starfire at the start of Incarnation: Chosen of Elune to consume Ascendant Fires.\n\n7. Cast Starfall to prevent capping on Astral Power or to consume Ascendant Eclipses at the start of Eclipse.\n\n8. Cast Wrath outside of Eclipse up to and including 6 targets.\n\n9. Cast Starfire in Lunar Eclipse and Wrath in Solar Eclipse.",
    ["DRUIDBALANCERAIDSTROTATION"] = "1. Apply Moonfire and refresh within pandemic.\n\n2. Apply Sunfire and refresh within pandemic.\n\n3. Press Force of Nature if you are not currently in an Eclipse and your next cast is either Solar Eclipse or Incarnation: Chosen of Elune.\n\n4. Press Incarnation: Chosen of Elune if you just used Force of Nature.\n\n5. Cast Starfire at the start of Incarnation: Chosen of Elune to consume Ascendant Fires.\n\n6. Enter Solar Eclipse whenever Starlord expires and you have any procs of Starweaver or Touch the Cosmos or you can overlap with Force of Nature.\n\n7. Cast Starfall to consume Starweaver's Warp or Touch the Cosmos.\n\n8. Cast Starsurge to prevent capping on Astral Power or to consume Ascendant Eclipses at the start of Solar Eclipse.\n\n9. Cast Wrath to generate Astral Power.",
    ["EVOKERAUGMENTATIONRAIDAOEROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Pre-cast Blistering Scales on a Tank.\n\n2. Pre-cast Living Flame.\n\n3. Cast Ebon Might.\n\n4. Cast Prescience on Buff Target 1. Use this time to position for Breath of Eons.\n\n5. Cast Prescience on Buff Target 2.\n\n6. Cast Breath of Eons. Aim for a short, safe flight path.\n\n7. Use trinket and Tempered Potion.\n\n8. Fire Breath at Rank 1.\n\n9. Cast Tip the Scales (off-GCD).\n\n10. Upheaval at Max Rank from Tip the Scales.\n\n11. Cast Eruption until dry on Essence, and fill with Living Flame as needed.\n\n12. Proceed onto the main rotation.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Maintain Prescience on chosen DPS players.\n\n2. Cast Ebon Might if a few seconds or less remain on the active buff duration.\n\n3. Cast Breath of Eons (see section on cooldown usage for more details).\n\n4. Cast Tip the Scales (see section on cooldown usage for more details).\n\n5. Cast Fire Breath at Rank 1.\n\n6. Cast Upheaval at Rank 1, unless increased radius is needed to hit relevant targets.\n\n7. Cast Eruption.\n\n8. Cast Living Flame as filler in nearly all situations.\n\n9. Cast Azure Strike as backup filler that can be cast while moving, or used to slow enemies.\n\n10. Maintain Blistering Scales on a Tank.",
    ["EVOKERAUGMENTATIONDUNGEONROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Pre-cast Blistering Scales on a Tank.\n\n2. Pre-cast Living Flame.\n\n3. Cast Ebon Might.\n\n4. Cast Prescience on Buff Target 1. Use this time to position for Breath of Eons.\n\n5. Cast Prescience on Buff Target 2.\n\n6. Cast Breath of Eons. Aim for a short, safe flight path.\n\n7. Use trinket and Tempered Potion.\n\n8. Fire Breath at Rank 1.\n\n9. Cast Tip the Scales (off-GCD).\n\n10. Upheaval at Max Rank from Tip the Scales.\n\n11. Cast Eruption until dry on Essence, and fill with Living Flame as needed.\n\n12. Proceed onto the main rotation.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Maintain Prescience on chosen DPS players.\n\n2. Cast Ebon Might if a few seconds or less remain on the active buff duration.\n\n3. Cast Breath of Eons (see section on cooldown usage for more details).\n\n4. Cast Tip the Scales (see section on cooldown usage for more details).\n\n5. Cast Fire Breath at Rank 1.\n\n6. Cast Upheaval at Rank 1, unless increased radius is needed to hit relevant targets.\n\n7. Cast Eruption.\n\n8. Cast Living Flame as filler in nearly all situations.\n\n9. Cast Azure Strike as backup filler that can be cast while moving, or used to slow enemies.\n\n10. Maintain Blistering Scales on a Tank.",
    ["EVOKERAUGMENTATIONDELVEROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Pre-cast Blistering Scales on a Tank.\n\n2. Pre-cast Living Flame.\n\n3. Cast Ebon Might.\n\n4. Cast Prescience on Buff Target 1. Use this time to position for Breath of Eons.\n\n5. Cast Prescience on Buff Target 2.\n\n6. Cast Breath of Eons. Aim for a short, safe flight path.\n\n7. Use trinket and Tempered Potion.\n\n8. Fire Breath at Rank 1.\n\n9. Cast Tip the Scales (off-GCD).\n\n10. Upheaval at Max Rank from Tip the Scales.\n\n11. Cast Eruption until dry on Essence, and fill with Living Flame as needed.\n\n12. Proceed onto the main rotation.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Maintain Prescience on chosen DPS players.\n\n2. Cast Ebon Might if a few seconds or less remain on the active buff duration.\n\n3. Cast Breath of Eons (see section on cooldown usage for more details).\n\n4. Cast Tip the Scales (see section on cooldown usage for more details).\n\n5. Cast Fire Breath at Rank 1.\n\n6. Cast Upheaval at Rank 1, unless increased radius is needed to hit relevant targets.\n\n7. Cast Eruption.\n\n8. Cast Living Flame as filler in nearly all situations.\n\n9. Cast Azure Strike as backup filler that can be cast while moving, or used to slow enemies.\n\n10. Maintain Blistering Scales on a Tank.",
    ["EVOKERAUGMENTATIONRAIDSTROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Pre-cast Blistering Scales on a Tank.\n\n2. Pre-cast Living Flame.\n\n3. Cast Ebon Might.\n\n4. Cast Prescience on Buff Target 1. Use this time to position for Breath of Eons.\n\n5. Cast Prescience on Buff Target 2.\n\n6. Cast Breath of Eons. Aim for a short, safe flight path.\n\n7. Use trinket and Tempered Potion.\n\n8. Fire Breath at Rank 1.\n\n9. Cast Tip the Scales (off-GCD).\n\n10. Upheaval at Max Rank from Tip the Scales.\n\n11. Cast Eruption until dry on Essence, and fill with Living Flame as needed.\n\n12. Proceed onto the main rotation.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Maintain Prescience on chosen DPS players.\n\n2. Cast Ebon Might if a few seconds or less remain on the active buff duration.\n\n3. Cast Breath of Eons (see section on cooldown usage for more details).\n\n4. Cast Tip the Scales (see section on cooldown usage for more details).\n\n5. Cast Fire Breath at Rank 1.\n\n6. Cast Upheaval at Rank 1, unless increased radius is needed to hit relevant targets.\n\n7. Cast Eruption.\n\n8. Cast Living Flame as filler in nearly all situations.\n\n9. Cast Azure Strike as backup filler that can be cast while moving, or used to slow enemies.\n\n10. Maintain Blistering Scales on a Tank.",
    ["EVOKERDEVASTATIONDUNGEONROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Hover twice before combat.\n\n2. Pre-cast Living Flame.\n\n3. Use damage potion.\n\n4. AoE Only: Use Vaelgor's Final Stare.\n\n5. Deep Breath.\n\n6. Dragonrage.\n\n7. Tip the Scales.\n\n8. Eternity Surge.\n\n9. Fire Breath Rank 1.\n\n10. AoE Only: Deep Breath again.\n\n11. Channel Disintegrate.\n\n12. Dragonrage is now active, continue to the normal rotation.\n\n13. Outside of AoE: Delay your damage trinket (ex: Vaelgor's Final Stare) until you have 4 stacks of Rising Fury.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Hover if capped and Deep Breath is ready soon.\n\n2. Deep Breath.\n\n3. Dragonrage.\n\n4. Tip the Scales on Eternity Surge.\n\n5. Fire Breath Rank 1.\n\n6. Eternity Surge Rank 1.\n\n7. Deep Breath with Strafing Run.\n\n8. Channel Disintegrate with Mass Disintegrate.\n\n9. Pyre at 4+ targets.\n\n10. Otherwise, channel Disintegrate.\n\n11. Azure Sweep.\n\n12. Living Flame with Leaping Flames and Burnout.\n\n13. Azure Strike as filler.",
    ["EVOKERDEVASTATIONDELVEROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Hover twice before combat.\n\n2. Pre-cast Living Flame.\n\n3. Use damage potion.\n\n4. AoE Only: Use Vaelgor's Final Stare.\n\n5. Deep Breath.\n\n6. Dragonrage.\n\n7. Tip the Scales.\n\n8. Eternity Surge.\n\n9. Fire Breath Rank 1.\n\n10. AoE Only: Deep Breath again.\n\n11. Channel Disintegrate.\n\n12. Dragonrage is now active, continue to the normal rotation.\n\n13. Outside of AoE: Delay your damage trinket (ex: Vaelgor's Final Stare) until you have 4 stacks of Rising Fury.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Hover if capped and Deep Breath is ready soon.\n\n2. Deep Breath.\n\n3. Dragonrage.\n\n4. Tip the Scales on Eternity Surge.\n\n5. Fire Breath Rank 1.\n\n6. Eternity Surge Rank 1.\n\n7. Deep Breath with Strafing Run.\n\n8. Channel Disintegrate with Mass Disintegrate.\n\n9. Pyre at 4+ targets.\n\n10. Otherwise, channel Disintegrate.\n\n11. Azure Sweep.\n\n12. Living Flame with Leaping Flames and Burnout.\n\n13. Azure Strike as filler.",
    ["EVOKERDEVASTATIONRAIDAOEROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Hover twice before combat.\n\n2. Pre-cast Living Flame.\n\n3. Use damage potion.\n\n4. AoE Only: Use Vaelgor's Final Stare.\n\n5. Deep Breath.\n\n6. Dragonrage.\n\n7. Tip the Scales.\n\n8. Eternity Surge.\n\n9. Fire Breath Rank 1.\n\n10. AoE Only: Deep Breath again.\n\n11. Channel Disintegrate.\n\n12. Dragonrage is now active, continue to the normal rotation.\n\n13. Outside of AoE: Delay your damage trinket (ex: Vaelgor's Final Stare) until you have 4 stacks of Rising Fury.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Hover if capped and Deep Breath is ready soon.\n\n2. Deep Breath.\n\n3. Dragonrage.\n\n4. Tip the Scales on Eternity Surge.\n\n5. Fire Breath Rank 1.\n\n6. Eternity Surge Rank 1.\n\n7. Deep Breath with Strafing Run.\n\n8. Channel Disintegrate with Mass Disintegrate.\n\n9. Pyre at 4+ targets.\n\n10. Otherwise, channel Disintegrate.\n\n11. Azure Sweep.\n\n12. Living Flame with Leaping Flames and Burnout.\n\n13. Azure Strike as filler.",
    ["EVOKERDEVASTATIONRAIDSTROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Hover twice before combat.\n\n2. Pre-cast Living Flame.\n\n3. Use damage potion.\n\n4. AoE Only: Use Vaelgor's Final Stare.\n\n5. Deep Breath.\n\n6. Dragonrage.\n\n7. Tip the Scales.\n\n8. Eternity Surge.\n\n9. Fire Breath Rank 1.\n\n10. AoE Only: Deep Breath again.\n\n11. Channel Disintegrate.\n\n12. Dragonrage is now active, continue to the normal rotation.\n\n13. Outside of AoE: Delay your damage trinket (ex: Vaelgor's Final Stare) until you have 4 stacks of Rising Fury.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Hover if capped and Deep Breath is ready soon.\n\n2. Deep Breath.\n\n3. Deep Breath when Strafing Run is about to expire.\n\n4. Dragonrage.\n\n5. Tip the Scales.\n\n6. Eternity Surge Rank 1.\n\n7. Fire Breath Rank 1.\n\n8. Channel Disintegrate with Mass Disintegrate.\n\n9. Channel Disintegrate.\n\n10. Azure Sweep.\n\n11. Living Flame as filler.\n\n12. Azure Strike if needed for movement.",
    ["EVOKERPRESERVATIONRAIDROTATION"] = "1. Cast Temporal Anomaly on cooldown.\n\n2. Cast Dream Breath often. Cast it after you have consumed Echo buffs to avoid consuming them with Dream Breath.\n\n3. Cast Verdant Embrace within a 15-second window.\n\n4. Cast Emerald Blossom if you have an Essence Burst.\n\n5. Cast Echo if you have Essence available and either no Essence Burst buff or you are at two stacks of Twin Echoes.\n\n6. Consume Echo buffs with Merithra's Blessing (common) or Verdant Embrace (rare).\n\n7. Cast Living Flame on the boss to farm Essence Bursts and contribute a little damage. You get a large mana refund if you cast it on an enemy instead of an ally.",
    ["EVOKERPRESERVATIONDUNGEONROTATION"] = "When heavy damage is coming up, you can use your Echo spell to put larger Echo buffs on your party. You can usually prioritize two DPS in your party plus yourself, since the tank is not usually vulnerable to the same type of AoE damage as the rest of your party. Then, cast Verdant Embrace on whoever you didn't Echo. The Verdant Embrace cast is copied to your three Echo targets, and all four of you will get a massive heal and a solid 8-second heal-over-time effect afterward.\n\nFitting in Your Other Spells\nThose will make up quite a lot of your healing, but we have a few more useful spells too. Here are some common scenarios where they'll be useful:\n\nDream Breath: Key Cast. Cast on cooldown at Rank 1 if damage is low to moderate. Cast at Rank 3 if you require a burst heal.\n\nFire Breath: Key Cast. Massive AoE damage ability that'll also heal the party for a lot via the Leaping Flames or Life-Giver's Flame talents. Cast at Rank 1 for the longer DoT unless you need the immediate burst damage of a higher rank.\n\nTime Dilation: Superb damage reduction for a single target. Low cooldown, so use this regularly on the tank or whoever is targeted by a \"tank-buster\" mechanic.\n\nZephyr: Cast before AoE damage to reduce how much damage the group takes. You'll generally need to play through a dungeon a few times to pick out the best spots for it.",
    ["EVOKERPRESERVATIONDELVEROTATION"] = "When heavy damage is coming up, you can use your Echo spell to put larger Echo buffs on your party. You can usually prioritize two DPS in your party plus yourself, since the tank is not usually vulnerable to the same type of AoE damage as the rest of your party. Then, cast Verdant Embrace on whoever you didn't Echo. The Verdant Embrace cast is copied to your three Echo targets, and all four of you will get a massive heal and a solid 8-second heal-over-time effect afterward.\n\nFitting in Your Other Spells\nThose will make up quite a lot of your healing, but we have a few more useful spells too. Here are some common scenarios where they'll be useful:\n\nDream Breath: Key Cast. Cast on cooldown at Rank 1 if damage is low to moderate. Cast at Rank 3 if you require a burst heal.\n\nFire Breath: Key Cast. Massive AoE damage ability that'll also heal the party for a lot via the Leaping Flames or Life-Giver's Flame talents. Cast at Rank 1 for the longer DoT unless you need the immediate burst damage of a higher rank.\n\nTime Dilation: Superb damage reduction for a single target. Low cooldown, so use this regularly on the tank or whoever is targeted by a \"tank-buster\" mechanic.\n\nZephyr: Cast before AoE damage to reduce how much damage the group takes. You'll generally need to play through a dungeon a few times to pick out the best spots for it.",
    ["HUNTERBEASTMASTERYDUNGEONROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Before pull, apply Hunter's Mark on your priority target.\n\n2. Cast Misdirection on your tank.\n\n3. Pre-cast Algeth'ar Puzzle Box two seconds before the pull.\n\n4. As pull starts, cast Barbed Shot.\n\n5. Use your potion, stat-boosting racials, and other trinkets.\n\n6. Cast Bestial Wrath. Make sure your pet is attacking your target by now!\n\n7. Cast Kill Command.\n\n8. Cast Barbed Shot.\n\n9. Proceed with the rest of your rotation like normal.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Cast Barbed Shot at your priority target if Bestial Wrath is about to come off cooldown.\n\n2. Cast Wild Thrash.\n\n3. Cast Bestial Wrath.\n\n4. Cast Kill Command.\n\n5. Cast Cobra Shot if you have the buff from Hogstrider active and you're facing fewer than 4 enemies.\n\n6. Cast Barbed Shot at your priority target.\n\n7. Cast Cobra Shot.",
    ["HUNTERBEASTMASTERYDELVEROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Before pull, apply Hunter's Mark on your priority target.\n\n2. Cast Misdirection on your tank.\n\n3. Pre-cast Algeth'ar Puzzle Box two seconds before the pull.\n\n4. As pull starts, cast Barbed Shot.\n\n5. Use your potion, stat-boosting racials, and other trinkets.\n\n6. Cast Bestial Wrath. Make sure your pet is attacking your target by now!\n\n7. Cast Kill Command.\n\n8. Cast Barbed Shot.\n\n9. Proceed with the rest of your rotation like normal.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Cast Barbed Shot at your priority target if Bestial Wrath is about to come off cooldown.\n\n2. Cast Wild Thrash.\n\n3. Cast Bestial Wrath.\n\n4. Cast Kill Command.\n\n5. Cast Cobra Shot if you have the buff from Hogstrider active and you're facing fewer than 4 enemies.\n\n6. Cast Barbed Shot at your priority target.\n\n7. Cast Cobra Shot.",
    ["HUNTERBEASTMASTERYRAIDAOEROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Before pull, apply Hunter's Mark on your priority target.\n\n2. Cast Misdirection on your tank.\n\n3. Pre-cast Algeth'ar Puzzle Box two seconds before the pull.\n\n4. As pull starts, cast Barbed Shot.\n\n5. Use your potion, stat-boosting racials, and other trinkets.\n\n6. Cast Bestial Wrath. Make sure your pet is attacking your target by now!\n\n7. Cast Kill Command.\n\n8. Cast Barbed Shot.\n\n9. Proceed with the rest of your rotation like normal.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Cast Barbed Shot at your priority target if Bestial Wrath is about to come off cooldown.\n\n2. Cast Wild Thrash.\n\n3. Cast Bestial Wrath.\n\n4. Cast Kill Command.\n\n5. Cast Cobra Shot if you have the buff from Hogstrider active and you're facing fewer than 4 enemies.\n\n6. Cast Barbed Shot at your priority target.\n\n7. Cast Cobra Shot.",
    ["HUNTERBEASTMASTERYRAIDSTROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Before pull, apply Hunter's Mark on your priority target.\n\n2. Cast Misdirection on your tank.\n\n3. Pre-cast Algeth'ar Puzzle Box two seconds before the pull.\n\n4. As pull starts, cast Barbed Shot.\n\n5. Use your potion, stat-boosting racials, and other trinkets.\n\n6. Cast Bestial Wrath. Make sure your pet is attacking your target by now!\n\n7. Cast Kill Command.\n\n8. Cast Barbed Shot.\n\n9. Proceed with the rest of your rotation like normal.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Cast Barbed Shot if Bestial Wrath is about to come off cooldown in the next 3 seconds.\n\n2. Cast Bestial Wrath.\n\n3. Cast Kill Command if you have a Howl of the Pack Leader buff or Nature's Ally active.\n\n4. Cast Barbed Shot.\n\n5. Cast Cobra Shot.",
    ["HUNTERMARKSMANSHIPDUNGEONROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n\n1. Ensure Hunter's Mark is active on the highest-health target from you or another Hunter in the group!\n\n2. Pre-cast Aimed Shot around 2.5 seconds before combat begins.\n\n3. Cast Arcane Shot.\n\n4. Cast Rapid Fire.\n\n5. Cast Arcane Shot.\n\n6. Activate Trueshot.\n\n7. Cast Aimed Shot.\n\n8. Cast Volley.\n\n9. Cast Arcane Shot.\n\n10. Cast Aimed Shot.\n\n11. Cast Arcane Shot.\n\n12. Cast Moonlight Chakram.\n\n13. Continue your normal rotation.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\nPriority List\nActivate Trueshot, your major cooldown. We ideally press Trueshot right before we normally intend to Aimed Shot, and ideally, right or shortly after a Rapid Fire, so that you carry a fresh Bulletstorm into your cooldowns.\n\nCast Volley on cooldown. Its main role is doing a bit of damage for us, while activating Trick Shots.\n\nCast Rapid Fire if you do not currently have the Bulletstorm buff active.\n\nCast Aimed Shot whenever it's available.\n\nCast Rapid Fire whenever it's available.\n\nCast Death Chakram when you have less than 1.2 charges of Aimed Shot remaining, or if you have under 35 Focus. The practical goal is to not let its usage interfere with maximizing our Aimed Shot casts. Using it slightly late in Trueshot is fine.\n\nCast Multi-Shot to spend the Precise Shots stacks generated by Aimed Shot and Rapid Fire, and to activate Trick Shots.\n\nCast Steady Shot as a filler. Do not overlook the importance of filling every \"empty\" moment with these, as they generate significant Focus and Aimed Shot cooldown reduction.",
    ["HUNTERMARKSMANSHIPDELVEROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n\n1. Ensure Hunter's Mark is active on the highest-health target from you or another Hunter in the group!\n\n2. Pre-cast Aimed Shot around 2.5 seconds before combat begins.\n\n3. Cast Arcane Shot.\n\n4. Cast Rapid Fire.\n\n5. Cast Arcane Shot.\n\n6. Activate Trueshot.\n\n7. Cast Aimed Shot.\n\n8. Cast Volley.\n\n9. Cast Arcane Shot.\n\n10. Cast Aimed Shot.\n\n11. Cast Arcane Shot.\n\n12. Cast Moonlight Chakram.\n\n13. Continue your normal rotation.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\nPriority List\nActivate Trueshot, your major cooldown. We ideally press Trueshot right before we normally intend to Aimed Shot, and ideally, right or shortly after a Rapid Fire, so that you carry a fresh Bulletstorm into your cooldowns.\n\nCast Volley on cooldown. Its main role is doing a bit of damage for us, while activating Trick Shots.\n\nCast Rapid Fire if you do not currently have the Bulletstorm buff active.\n\nCast Aimed Shot whenever it's available.\n\nCast Rapid Fire whenever it's available.\n\nCast Death Chakram when you have less than 1.2 charges of Aimed Shot remaining, or if you have under 35 Focus. The practical goal is to not let its usage interfere with maximizing our Aimed Shot casts. Using it slightly late in Trueshot is fine.\n\nCast Multi-Shot to spend the Precise Shots stacks generated by Aimed Shot and Rapid Fire, and to activate Trick Shots.\n\nCast Steady Shot as a filler. Do not overlook the importance of filling every \"empty\" moment with these, as they generate significant Focus and Aimed Shot cooldown reduction.",
    ["HUNTERMARKSMANSHIPRAIDAOEROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n\n1. Ensure Hunter's Mark is active on the highest-health target from you or another Hunter in the group!\n\n2. Pre-cast Aimed Shot around 2.5 seconds before combat begins.\n\n3. Cast Arcane Shot.\n\n4. Cast Rapid Fire.\n\n5. Cast Arcane Shot.\n\n6. Activate Trueshot.\n\n7. Cast Aimed Shot.\n\n8. Cast Volley.\n\n9. Cast Arcane Shot.\n\n10. Cast Aimed Shot.\n\n11. Cast Arcane Shot.\n\n12. Cast Moonlight Chakram.\n\n13. Continue your normal rotation.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\nPriority List\nActivate Trueshot, your major cooldown. We ideally press Trueshot right before we normally intend to Aimed Shot, and ideally, right or shortly after a Rapid Fire, so that you carry a fresh Bulletstorm into your cooldowns.\n\nCast Volley on cooldown. Its main role is doing a bit of damage for us, while activating Trick Shots.\n\nCast Rapid Fire if you do not currently have the Bulletstorm buff active.\n\nCast Aimed Shot whenever it's available.\n\nCast Rapid Fire whenever it's available.\n\nCast Death Chakram when you have less than 1.2 charges of Aimed Shot remaining, or if you have under 35 Focus. The practical goal is to not let its usage interfere with maximizing our Aimed Shot casts. Using it slightly late in Trueshot is fine.\n\nCast Multi-Shot to spend the Precise Shots stacks generated by Aimed Shot and Rapid Fire, and to activate Trick Shots.\n\nCast Steady Shot as a filler. Do not overlook the importance of filling every \"empty\" moment with these, as they generate significant Focus and Aimed Shot cooldown reduction.",
    ["HUNTERMARKSMANSHIPRAIDSTROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n\n1. Ensure Hunter's Mark is active on the highest-health target from you or another Hunter in the group!\n\n2. Pre-cast Aimed Shot around 2.5 seconds before combat begins.\n\n3. Cast Arcane Shot.\n\n4. Cast Rapid Fire.\n\n5. Cast Arcane Shot.\n\n6. Activate Trueshot.\n\n7. Cast Aimed Shot.\n\n8. Cast Volley.\n\n9. Cast Arcane Shot.\n\n10. Cast Aimed Shot.\n\n11. Cast Arcane Shot.\n\n12. Cast Moonlight Chakram.\n\n13. Continue your normal rotation.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\nActivate Trueshot, your major cooldown. We ideally press Trueshot right before we normally intend to Aimed Shot, and ideally, right or shortly after a Rapid Fire, so that you carry a fresh Bulletstorm into your cooldowns.\n\nCast Volley on cooldown. On single-target, its main role is doing a bit of damage for us.\n\nCast Rapid Fire if you do not currently have the Bulletstorm buff active.\n\nCast Aimed Shot whenever it's available.\n\nCast Rapid Fire whenever it's available.\n\nCast Death Chakram when you have less than 1.2 charges of Aimed Shot remaining, or if you have under 35 Focus.\n\nCast Arcane Shot to spend the Precise Shots stacks generated by Aimed Shot and Rapid Fire.\n\nCast Steady Shot as a filler. Fill every \"empty\" moment with these to generate Focus.",
    ["HUNTERSURVIVALDUNGEONROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Pre-cast Hatchet Toss ~1 GCD (~1.25sec) before the pull timer ends, making sure to stand far away from the boss.\n\n2. Cast Takedown and Harpoon together.\n\n3. Cast Wildfire Bomb.\n\n4. Cast Boomstick.\n\n5. Cast Kill Command.\n\n6. Cast Wildfire Bomb.\n\n7. Cast Moonlight Chakram.\n\n8. Continue by following your Single Target priority.\n\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Cast Hunter's Mark if it is not yet active. \n\n2. Cast Kill Command whenever you run out of Tip of the Spear stacks.\n\n3. Cast Boomstick.\n\n4. Cast Wildfire Bomb with Tip of the Spear in the following circumstances:\n   * Whenever your target is affected by Sentinel's Mark.\n   * Whenever Wildfire Bomb is less than 6 seconds away from fully recharging its second charge.\n\n5. Cast Kill Command once before entering Takedown to maximize Tip of the Spear stacks.\n\n6. Cast Takedown if you have a Tip of the Spear stack to spend.\n\n7. Cast Moonlight Chakram if you have a Tip of the Spear stack to spend.\n\n8. Cast Raptor Swipe if you have a Tip of the Spear stack to spend.\n\n9. Cast Raptor Strike with or without a Tip of the Spear stack to spend.",
    ["HUNTERSURVIVALRAIDAOEROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Pre-cast Hatchet Toss ~1 GCD (~1.25sec) before the pull timer ends, making sure to stand far away from the boss.\n\n2. Cast Takedown and Harpoon together.\n\n3. Cast Wildfire Bomb.\n\n4. Cast Boomstick.\n\n5. Cast Kill Command.\n\n6. Cast Wildfire Bomb.\n\n7. Cast Moonlight Chakram.\n\n8. Continue by following your Single Target priority.\n\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Cast Hunter's Mark if it is not yet active. \n\n2. Cast Kill Command whenever you run out of Tip of the Spear stacks.\n\n3. Cast Boomstick.\n\n4. Cast Wildfire Bomb with Tip of the Spear in the following circumstances:\n   * Whenever your target is affected by Sentinel's Mark.\n   * Whenever Wildfire Bomb is less than 6 seconds away from fully recharging its second charge.\n\n5. Cast Kill Command once before entering Takedown to maximize Tip of the Spear stacks.\n\n6. Cast Takedown if you have a Tip of the Spear stack to spend.\n\n7. Cast Moonlight Chakram if you have a Tip of the Spear stack to spend.\n\n8. Cast Raptor Swipe if you have a Tip of the Spear stack to spend.\n\n9. Cast Raptor Strike with or without a Tip of the Spear stack to spend.",
    ["HUNTERSURVIVALDELVEROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Pre-cast Hatchet Toss ~1 GCD (~1.25sec) before the pull timer ends, making sure to stand far away from the boss.\n\n2. Cast Takedown and Harpoon together.\n\n3. Cast Wildfire Bomb.\n\n4. Cast Boomstick.\n\n5. Cast Kill Command.\n\n6. Cast Wildfire Bomb.\n\n7. Cast Moonlight Chakram.\n\n8. Continue by following your Single Target priority.\n\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Cast Hunter's Mark if it is not yet active. \n\n2. Cast Kill Command whenever you run out of Tip of the Spear stacks.\n\n3. Cast Boomstick.\n\n4. Cast Wildfire Bomb with Tip of the Spear in the following circumstances:\n   * Whenever your target is affected by Sentinel's Mark.\n   * Whenever Wildfire Bomb is less than 6 seconds away from fully recharging its second charge.\n\n5. Cast Kill Command once before entering Takedown to maximize Tip of the Spear stacks.\n\n6. Cast Takedown if you have a Tip of the Spear stack to spend.\n\n7. Cast Moonlight Chakram if you have a Tip of the Spear stack to spend.\n\n8. Cast Raptor Swipe if you have a Tip of the Spear stack to spend.\n\n9. Cast Raptor Strike with or without a Tip of the Spear stack to spend.",
    ["HUNTERSURVIVALRAIDSTROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n1. Pre-cast Hatchet Toss ~1 GCD (~1.25sec) before the pull timer ends, making sure to stand far away from the boss.\n\n2. Cast Takedown and Harpoon together.\n\n3. Cast Wildfire Bomb.\n\n4. Cast Boomstick.\n\n5. Cast Kill Command.\n\n6. Cast Wildfire Bomb.\n\n7. Cast Moonlight Chakram.\n\n8. Continue by following your Single Target priority.\n\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Cast Hunter's Mark if it is not yet active.\n\n2. Cast Kill Command whenever you run out of Tip of the Spear stacks.\n\n3. Cast Wildfire Bomb if your target is affected by Sentinel's Mark.\n\n4. Cast Boomstick if you have a Tip of the Spear stack to spend.\n\n5. Cast Wildfire Bomb if it is less than 6 seconds away from fully recharging its second charge.\n\n6. Cast Kill Command once before entering Takedown to maximize Tip of the Spear stacks.\n\n7. Cast Takedown if you have a Tip of the Spear stack to spend.\n\n8. Cast Moonlight Chakram.\n\n9. Cast Raptor Swipe if you have a Tip of the Spear stack to spend.\n\n10. Cast Raptor Strike with or without a Tip of the Spear stack to spend.",
    ["MAGEARCANEDUNGEONROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n\n1. Cast Arcane Blast 2 seconds before pulling.\n\n2. Cast Arcane Orb and Time Warp.\n\n3. Cast Arcane Blast until you have 20 stacks of Arcane Salvo.\n\n4. Use any potions, items, or trinkets that will buff you for more than 15 seconds.\n\n5. Cast Arcane Surge.\n\n6. Use any potions, items, or trinkets that will buff you for less than or equal to 15 seconds.\n\n7. Cast Arcane Barrage and then Touch of the Magi while it is mid-air.\n\n8. 45 seconds later, when Touch of the Magi's cooldown finishes, repeat the last step.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Cast Arcane Orb whenever you have just cast Arcane Barrage and have Clearcasting. \n\n2. Cast Arcane Barrage with 4x Arcane Charges if you have 20 stacks of Arcane Salvo. \n\n3. Cast Arcane Pulse if you have 3 or more targets. \n\n4. Cast Arcane Blast.\n\n5. Cast Arcane Barrage if you don't have enough mana for Arcane Blast.",
    ["MAGEARCANERAIDAOEROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n\n1. Cast Arcane Blast 2 seconds before pulling.\n\n2. Cast Arcane Orb and Time Warp.\n\n3. Cast Arcane Blast until you have 20 stacks of Arcane Salvo.\n\n4. Use any potions, items, or trinkets that will buff you for more than 15 seconds.\n\n5. Cast Arcane Surge.\n\n6. Use any potions, items, or trinkets that will buff you for less than or equal to 15 seconds.\n\n7. Cast Arcane Barrage and then Touch of the Magi while it is mid-air.\n\n8. 45 seconds later, when Touch of the Magi's cooldown finishes, repeat the last step.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Cast Arcane Orb whenever you have just cast Arcane Barrage and have Clearcasting. \n\n2. Cast Arcane Barrage with 4x Arcane Charges if you have 20 stacks of Arcane Salvo. \n\n3. Cast Arcane Pulse if you have 3 or more targets. \n\n4. Cast Arcane Blast.\n\n5. Cast Arcane Barrage if you don't have enough mana for Arcane Blast.",
    ["MAGEARCANEDELVEROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n\n1. Cast Arcane Blast 2 seconds before pulling.\n\n2. Cast Arcane Orb and Time Warp.\n\n3. Cast Arcane Blast until you have 20 stacks of Arcane Salvo.\n\n4. Use any potions, items, or trinkets that will buff you for more than 15 seconds.\n\n5. Cast Arcane Surge.\n\n6. Use any potions, items, or trinkets that will buff you for less than or equal to 15 seconds.\n\n7. Cast Arcane Barrage and then Touch of the Magi while it is mid-air.\n\n8. 45 seconds later, when Touch of the Magi's cooldown finishes, repeat the last step.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Cast Arcane Orb whenever you have just cast Arcane Barrage and have Clearcasting. \n\n2. Cast Arcane Barrage with 4x Arcane Charges if you have 20 stacks of Arcane Salvo. \n\n3. Cast Arcane Pulse if you have 3 or more targets. \n\n4. Cast Arcane Blast.\n\n5. Cast Arcane Barrage if you don't have enough mana for Arcane Blast.",
    ["MAGEARCANERAIDSTROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \n\n1. Cast Arcane Blast 2 seconds before pulling.\n\n2. Cast Arcane Orb and Time Warp.\n\n3. Cast Arcane Blast until you have 20 stacks of Arcane Salvo.\n\n4. Use any potions, items, or trinkets that will buff you for more than 15 seconds.\n\n5. Cast Arcane Surge.\n\n6. Use any potions, items, or trinkets that will buff you for less than or equal to 15 seconds.\n\n7. Cast Arcane Barrage and then Touch of the Magi while it is mid-air.\n\n8. 45 seconds later, when Touch of the Magi's cooldown finishes, repeat the last step.\n\n-ROTATION--\n\n1. Cast Arcane Orb whenever you have just cast Arcane Barrage and have Clearcasting. \n\n2. Cast Arcane Barrage with 4x Arcane Charges if you have 20 stacks of Arcane Salvo. \n\n3. Cast Arcane Pulse if you have 3 or more targets. \n\n4. Cast Arcane Blast.\n\n5. Cast Arcane Barrage if you don't have enough mana for Arcane Blast.",
    ["MAGEFIREDUNGEONROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \nOPENER (FIRESTARTER)\n\n[1] Pre-cast Pyroblast before the pull (hard-cast).\n[2] Fireball.\n[3] Fire Blast during the Fireball cast.\n[4] Pyroblast with Hot Streak! twice\n[5] Alternate between Fire Blast and Pyroblast until you run out of charges.\n[6] If the target is still above 90% health, repeat the following:\n[1] Fireball\n[2] Fire Blast during the Fireball cast.\n[3] Without Hot Streak!, Fireball again.\n[4] Pyroblast with Hot Streak! twice\n\nENTERING COMBUSTION\n\n[1] Pyroblast to spend your Hot Streak!.\n[2] AoE Only: Precast Meteor, before your Scorch cast.\n[3] Begin a Scorch cast.\n[4] Fire Blast as soon as the Scorch cast begins.\n[5] Combustion right before the Scorch cast ends.\n[6] Pyroblast (or Flamestrike in AoE) with Hot Streak! twice\n\n-ROTATION--\n\nDuring Combustion, all of your casts will Critically strike. This means that you will alternate between Flamestrike (with Hot Streak!) and builders.\n\n[1] Meteor (if it will land during Combustion)\n[2] Flamestrike with Hot Streak!\n[3] Flamestrike again if you just spent Hot Streak! at the end of a Scorch cast.\n\nThe below casts are used to generate Hot Streak!:\n\nFire Blast.\n\nScorch as filler.\n\nPriority (Outside Combustion)\n\n[1] Meteor right before Combustion.\n[2] Cast Combustion.\n[3] Flamestrike with Hot Streak!.\n[4] Flamestrike with Hyperthermia.\n[5] Cast Fire Blast if you have Heating Up while casting Fireball.\n[6] Cast Fire Blast if you just spent Hot Streak! and are guaranteed to Crit: Flamestrike is in flight during Hyperthermia.\n[7] In Execute: Cast Fire Blast without Heating Up while casting Scorch.\n[8] In Execute: If you have Heating Up.\n[9] Scorch with Heat Shimmer after spending Hot Streak!.\n[10] In Execute: Scorch if the target is below 30% health.\n[11] Fireball as filler.",
    ["MAGEFIRERAIDAOEROTATION"] = "--OPENER-- \nOPENER (FIRESTARTER)\n\n[1] Pre-cast Pyroblast before the pull (hard-cast).\n[2] Fireball.\n[3] Fire Blast during the Fireball cast.\n[4] Pyroblast with Hot Streak! twice\n[5] Alternate between Fire Blast and Pyroblast until you run out of charges.\n[6] If the target is still above 90% health, repeat the following:\n[1] Fireball\n[2] Fire Blast during the Fireball cast.\n[3] Without Hot Streak!, Fireball again.\n[4] Pyroblast with Hot Streak! twice\n\nENTERING COMBUSTION\n\n[1] Pyroblast to spend your Hot Streak!.\n[2] AoE Only: Precast Meteor, before your Scorch cast.\n[3] Begin a Scorch cast.\n[4] Fire Blast as soon as the Scorch cast begins.\n[5] Combustion right before the Scorch cast ends.\n[6] Pyroblast (or Flamestrike in AoE) with Hot Streak! twice\n\n-ROTATION--\n\nDuring Combustion, all of your casts will Critically strike. This means that you will alternate between Flamestrike (with Hot Streak!) and builders.\n\n[1] Meteor (if it will land during Combustion)\n[2] Flamestrike with Hot Streak!\n[3] Flamestrike again if you just spent Hot Streak! at the end of a Scorch cast.\n\nThe below casts are used to generate Hot Streak!:\n\nFire Blast.\n\nScorch as filler.\n\nPriority (Outside Combustion)\n\n[1] Meteor right before Combustion.\n[2] Cast Combustion.\n[3] Flamestrike with Hot Streak!.\n[4] Flamestrike with Hyperthermia.\n[5] Cast Fire Blast if you have Heating Up while casting Fireball.\n[6] Cast Fire Blast if you just spent Hot Streak! and are guaranteed to Crit: Flamestrike is in flight during Hyperthermia.\n[7] In Execute: Cast Fire Blast without Heating Up while casting Scorch.\n[8] In Execute: If you have Heating Up.\n[9] Scorch with Heat Shimmer after spending Hot Streak!.\n[10] In Execute: Scorch if the target is below 30% health.\n[11] Fireball as filler.",
